---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'How SSDI Benefits Work | ssdicalc.com';
const description = 'A complete guide to SSDI eligibility requirements, how benefits are calculated, and how to apply.';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <h1>How SSDI Benefits Work</h1>
  <h2>Eligibility Requirements</h2>
  <p>To receive SSDI you must: (1) be unable to do substantial gainful activity due to a medically determinable impairment; (2) have a condition expected to last at least 12 months or result in death; and (3) have earned sufficient work credits.</p>
  <h2>The Five-Step Sequential Evaluation</h2>
  <p>SSA evaluates SSDI claims using a five-step process: (1) Are you working above SGA level? (2) Is your impairment severe? (3) Does your impairment meet a Blue Book listing? (4) Can you perform your past work? (5) Can you do any work in the national economy?</p>
  <h2>Benefit Amount</h2>
  <p>Your monthly SSDI benefit is your Primary Insurance Amount (PIA), calculated from your AIME. The 2025 average is ~$1,537/month; the maximum is $3,822/month.</p>
  <h2>Medicare</h2>
  <p>After 24 months of SSDI entitlement (not payment — entitlement starts at your disability onset date plus 5-month waiting period), you become eligible for Medicare, regardless of age.</p>
  <h2>Continuing Disability Reviews</h2>
  <p>SSA periodically reviews your case to verify you remain disabled. Reviews occur every 3 years for conditions expected to improve, every 7 years for conditions unlikely to improve.</p>
</BaseLayout>
